% Define the initial state: monkey is at the door, on the floor, without the banana.
initial_state(state(atDoor, onFloor, hasBanana, no)).

% Define an action where the monkey grasps the banana.
move(state(atDoor, onFloor, hasBanana, no), grasp, state(atDoor, onFloor, hasBanana, yes)).

% Additional actions can be defined similarly if needed.

% Example query to test the action and check the resulting state.
% Use: ?- move(state(atDoor, onFloor, hasBanana, no), Action, ResultingState).
